Package org.example

Class Program

java.lang.Object
org.example.Program
public class Program extends Object
The Program class represents a fitness program that clients can enroll in. It includes details about the program such as its title, duration, difficulty level, goals, schedule, content, price, and other related information.
Author:
Tala Alhendi

  • Constructor Details

    • Program

      public Program()
      Default constructor for the Program class. Initializes a predefined fitness program with default values. The program includes basic information such as title, duration, difficulty level, goals, multimedia content, schedule, and price. It also prepares the enrollment list for clients.

    • Program

      public Program(String title, String duration, String difficultyLevel, String goals, Content content, Schedule schedule, String price)
      Constructor for the Program class that initializes a custom fitness or educational program. The program is defined by its title, duration, difficulty level, goals, multimedia content, schedule, and price. It also initializes the list of enrolled clients.
      Parameters:
      title - the title of the program
      duration - the duration of the program (e.g., "4 weeks", "6 months")
      difficultyLevel - the difficulty level of the program (e.g., "Beginner", "Intermediate")
      goals - the goals of the program (e.g., "Weight Loss", "Skill Development")
      content - the multimedia content associated with the program (e.g., videos, images, tutorials)
      schedule - the schedule for the program, which includes days, time, and schedule type
      price - the price of the program
